<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-09T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="966" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7388</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-09T14:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mormon colonists about Casas Grandes in danger. With Columbus raid in
                            mind Villa avoided coming north. They are in greater danger his return
                            south. There are from 400 to 500 Mormons in the colonies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>